''AKA Degenerate Distribution''

<<probability_distribution_summary>>

$$ \displaystyle X \sim \delta_a$$

It is really just a non-random (i.e. deterministic) value!

This [[Distribution|Probability Distribution]] is actually pretty useful, because it allows to interpret a lot of elementary [[Probability|Probability Theory]] problems - e.g. given at job interviews (like the [[Monty Hall Problem]] and such) - using the framework of [[Statistical Hypothesis Testing]]. In such problems one is usually asked to calculate actual [[Probabilities|Probability Measure]] and/or values, which is exactly what this [[Distribution|Probability Distribution]] models!

